# Strapi Frontend Slug Contract

## **Overview**

Strapi normalizes UID `slug` fields to **lowercase kebab-case** on save. The Next.js app must use **canonical slug strings** in API filters and **unchanged** `article.slug` values in routes. Full reference: [strapi_frontend_slug_contract.md](mdc:documentation/strapi/strapi_frontend_slug_contract.md).

For populate, `publishedAt`, tenant scoping, and media extraction, see [strapi_5_api_patterns.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/strapi_5_api_patterns.mdc).

## **Canonical category slugs**

Import from [`src/lib/strapi/newsCategorySlugs.ts`](mdc:src/lib/strapi/newsCategorySlugs.ts) ‚Äî do not hardcode slug strings in fetchers.

| Section | Constant | API value |
|---------|----------|-----------|
| Main News | `STRAPI_NEWS_CATEGORY_SLUGS.mainNews` | `main-news` |
| Featured News | `STRAPI_NEWS_CATEGORY_SLUGS.featuredNews` | `featured-news` |
| Press Release | `STRAPI_NEWS_CATEGORY_SLUGS.pressRelease` | `press-release` |
| Most Read | `STRAPI_NEWS_CATEGORY_SLUGS.mostRead` | `most-read` |

Admin display names (`Main News`) are **not** API slugs.

## **Category filter in article queries**

### **DO: Use shared helper with `$eq` (production)**

```typescript
import {
  STRAPI_NEWS_CATEGORY_SLUGS,
  buildCategorySlugFilter,
} from '@/lib/strapi/newsCategorySlugs';

buildArticleQuery(
  buildCategorySlugFilter(STRAPI_NEWS_CATEGORY_SLUGS.mainNews),
  'publishedAt:desc',
  10,
  tenantFilter
);
```

### **DO: Use `$eqi` only for legacy mixed-case data**

```typescript
buildCategorySlugFilter(STRAPI_NEWS_CATEGORY_SLUGS.mainNews, { caseInsensitive: true });
```

### **DON'T**

```typescript
// ‚ùå DON'T: Invent casing or match display names
'filters[category][slug][$eq]=Main-News'

// ‚ùå DON'T: Duplicate slug literals across files
'filters[category][slug][$eqi]=main-news'

// ‚ùå DON'T: Re-slug article URLs on read
`/news/${article.slug.toLowerCase().replace(/ /g, '-')}`
```

## **Article routes and links**

- **DO:** Use `article.slug` from the API as returned in hrefs (e.g. `/mosc-redesign/news/${slug}`).
- **DON'T:** Uppercase, trim-case, or kebab-normalize slugs when **reading** API data.
- **Optional:** Use `toKebabSlug()` from `newsCategorySlugs.ts` only when **POSTing** content to Strapi.

## **Required query parts (news lists)**

Always combine category filters with:

- `filters[tenant][tenantId][$eq]=<NEXT_PUBLIC_TENANT_ID>` (and optional `documentId` OR ‚Äî see news fetcher)
- `filters[publishedAt][$notNull]=true`
- Array-style populate ‚Äî see [strapi_5_api_patterns.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/strapi_5_api_patterns.mdc)

## **Directory and other content types**

Bishops, parishes, dioceses, etc. use the same kebab-case rule: `filters[slug][$eq]=...` with slug values from API responses.

## **Checklist (news integration)**

- [ ] Category fetches use `STRAPI_NEWS_CATEGORY_SLUGS` + `buildCategorySlugFilter`
- [ ] Default operator is `$eq` after Strapi slug backfill on Cloud
- [ ] Article detail links use API `slug` unchanged
- [ ] Tenant + published filters on every article list
- [ ] Section anchor IDs (`#main-news`) are UI-only; they are not Strapi filter values

